             lodged at our house. On the 2d of June the prisoner came and said he had just left Mr. Jeffries in Tower-street, and he had directed him to bring that bill to me to pay; (producing one) - he receipted the bill, and said I might depend upon it it was quite correct, Mr. Jeffries owed him the money for moving some goods; it was 3 s., which I paid him. Here is the receipt, which he wrote it presence - I am certain he is the man.</p>
